I try to be a loyal customer because their food is good, but these people are tricky and add extra costs and fees into the bill without telling you. As a consumer, I will take my business elsewhere - to a honest business that doesn’t try to get over on their customers. This technique is called “salami slicing”- when you steal a little extra from each customer (that they don’t notice), but ultimately it adds up for the business owner. This is a shady practice and would result in a Better Business Bureau violation/fine. Dominican restaurants are notorious for providing terrible customer service and nickel and dining their customers. If you want to do business in the USA, you can’t have a third world mentality and try to get over on your customers!!!!!

This place is amazing. We had my fathers 75th birthday party catered by Caridad and I am very very happy that we decided to use them. After many phone calls shopping around for the best deal, these guys had great prices and the food was DELICIOUS!!!! We ordered two large Morros, one morro de guandules, one morro de habichuela negra.. both were very good. We also ordered Chicharron de pollo and rotisserie chicken. I’m telling you the food was so well seasoned. Not to mention that the staff here is incredibly friendly!! The manager gave me a complimentary piña colada while I waited for the chicken to be packed up. AND they helped me out to my car with the huuuuge trays of food that I thoroughly felt I got an amazing deal on.  The huge trays of rice were just $50 when everywhere else was $65. I never have my parties catered as usually we do it potluck style and everyone in the family brings a dish. But we decided to do a little different this time, and I do not regret it one bit. Even came from Teaneck New Jersey into the city and I would do it again in a heartbeat! Thank you thank you thank you guys so so much for helping our party be a huge success. My dad and family were super super happy and we had an amazing time! Thank you Caridad!!
